Sure, that'd be fine, but just construct it like normal

std::string location(resp.getHeaderValue("Location"));

At some point, now that we're not really modifying in place, addPrefixToStringItem should probably just return the new string instead of completely replacing it with a copy.

No, I'm saying that the Location header needs the prefix appended.  We shouldn't be blindly copying it here.

I think what you want here is

std::string_view header = resp.getHeaderValue(boost::beast::http::field::location);
if (header.empty()){
   std::string location(header);
   addPrefixToStringItem(location, prefix);
   asyncResp.addHeader(boost::beast::http::field::location, location);
}

Otherwise we're passing the header through, just to look it up again, right?
